    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Meter_SelectByFacility",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve detailed information about meters associated with a specific facility. It joins several tables within the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema to compile a comprehensive dataset that includes meter details, account information, energy delivery types, meter statuses, and utility company descriptions. The procedure filters results based on the facility's sequence ID and ensures that only active accounts and meters are considered."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this stored procedure is medium. It involves multiple table joins and a variety of fields from different tables, which requires a good understanding of the database schema. The use of transaction isolation level and handling of multiple attributes adds to its complexity."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "@FacilitySeqId AS INT",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ": This parameter is used to specify the unique identifier of the facility for which the meter information is being requested. It acts as a filter to ensure that only meters associated with the specified facility are retrieved."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The procedure begins by setting "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "NOCOUNT ON",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to prevent the sending of DONE_IN_PROC messages, which can reduce network traffic."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "It sets the transaction isolation level to "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", allowing the query to read uncommitted changes from other transactions. This can help improve performance by reducing locking but at the risk of reading dirty data."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The main query retrieves a wide range of meter-related data by joining the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Account",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Facility",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Meter",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "EnergyDeliveryType",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "AccountMeterStatus",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "UtilityCompany",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " tables."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The query filters for active accounts and meters ("
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A.IsActive = 1",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "M.IsActive = 1",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ") and matches the facility sequence ID with the provided parameter."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The results are ordered by the current account number and meter number, providing a structured output."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "5. Performance Considerations"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The use of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " isolation level can improve performance by reducing locking overhead, but it may lead to reading uncommitted or dirty data."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The procedure involves multiple joins, which can be resource-intensive, especially if the tables involved are large. Indexes on join columns ("
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "FacilitySeqid",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "UniqueAccountSeqID",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", etc.) can help optimize performance."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The selection of a large number of columns may lead to increased I/O and network traffic, which could impact performance if the result set is large."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "6. Potential Issues or Risks"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulletList",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The use of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "READ UNCOMMITTED",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " can lead to reading inconsistent data due to uncommitted transactions, which might not be suitable for all business scenarios."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The procedure assumes that all necessary indexes are in place for optimal performance. Lack of proper indexing could lead to slow query execution."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "If the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "FacilitySeqId",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "code"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " parameter is not validated before being passed to the procedure, it could lead to unexpected results or errors."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The procedure does not handle exceptions or errors, which could result in unhandled exceptions if issues arise during execution."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "listItem",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The procedure retrieves a large number of columns, which may not be necessary for all use cases, potentially leading to inefficient data retrieval."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "7. Stored Procedure Definition"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "codeBlock",
      "attrs": {
        "language": "sql"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CREATE PROCEDURE [Billing].[usp_Meter_SelectByFacility]\n(\r\n\t@FacilitySeqId AS INT\r\n)\r\nAS\r\nBEGIN\r\n\tSET NOCOUNT ON;\r\n\tSET TRANSACTION ISOLATION LEVEL READ UNCOMMITTED;\r\n\r\n\tSELECT M.MeterSeqid\r\n\t\t,A.CurrentAccountNumber AS OriginalAccountNumber\r\n        ,M.UtilityServiceAddress\r\n        ,M.CurrentMeterNumber\r\n        ,M.OriginalMeterNumber\r\n        ,M.NgridCorrectorMeterId\r\n        ,M.Tension\r\n        ,M.IsOECDefinedMeter\r\n        ,M.IsUploadProcessed\r\n        ,M.IsMeterUsageTracked\r\n        ,M.EnergySource\r\n        ,M.EnergyAccountDescription\r\n        ,M.MeterStatus + ' - ' + AMS.ShortDesc AS MeterStatus\r\n        ,M.MeterPreviousStatus\r\n        ,M.MeterStatusCodePeriod\r\n        ,M.AssociatedDemandMeter\r\n        ,M.AgencyELOMeterLocation\r\n        ,M.UtilityAddressMeterLocation\r\n        ,M.MeterSquareFootageCoverage\r\n        ,M.TurnOnDate\r\n        ,M.TurnOffDate\r\n        ,M.MeterEffectiveOnDate\r\n        ,M.MeterEffectiveOffDate\r\n        ,M.MeterType\r\n        ,M.MeterDials\r\n        ,M.MeterConstant\r\n        ,M.LastPeriodOriginalBilled\r\n        ,M.LastPeriodAdjustmentBilled\r\n        ,M.LastZeroUsageBillingPeriod\r\n        ,M.AdjustmentRecordSeqid\r\n        ,M.AMRIndicator\r\n        ,M.FireAuditTrigger\r\n        ,M.Notes\r\n        ,M.AuthenticatedUserID\r\n        ,M.DateAdded\r\n        ,M.LastUpdate\r\n        ,M.UniqueMeterSeqid\r\n        ,M.IsCurrentRecord\r\n        ,M.RecordVersion\r\n        ,M.IsActive\r\n        ,M.UniqueAccountSeqID\r\n\t\t,EDT.[Description] + ' (' + EDT.EnergyType + ')' AS EnergyType\r\n\t\t,A.AccountSeqid AS AccountSeqId\r\n\t\t,UC.ShortDesc AS UtilityCompany\r\n\tFROM Billing.Account AS A\r\n\t\tINNER JOIN Billing.Facility AS F ON A.FacilityAccount = F.FacilitySeqid\r\n\t\tINNER JOIN Billing.Meter AS M ON M.UniqueAccountSeqID = A.UniqueAccountSeqid\r\n\t\tINNER JOIN Billing.EnergyDeliveryType AS EDT ON EDT.EnergyDeliveryType = A.EnergySource\r\n\t\tINNER JOIN Billing.AccountMeterStatus AS AMS ON M.MeterStatus = AMS.AccountMeterStatus\r\n\t\tINNER JOIN Billing.UtilityCompany AS UC ON UC.UtilityCompanySeqid = A.UtilityAccountProvider\r\n\tWHERE A.IsActive = 1\r\n\t\tAND M.IsActive = 1\r\n\t\tAND F.[FacilitySeqid] = @FacilitySeqId\r\n\tORDER BY A.CurrentAccountNumber, M.CurrentMeterNumber;\r\nEND;"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}